-- Czech Stocks: Erste Group Bank, Komercni Banka Move in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-02-16T16:13:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-16/czech-stocks-erste-group-bank-komercni-banka-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
dropped 1.1 percent to 995.9 at the close in Prague.  The following are among the most active  equities  on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Erste Group Bank AG (RBAG)   retreated 0.8 percent to 467
koruna. The Austrian lender earlier slid as much as 4.8 percent
after Moody’s Investors Service said it may cut its credit
ratings.  Komercni Banka AS (KOMB)   declined 2.4 percent to 3,590
koruna after fourth-quarter profit and proposed dividend posted
by the unit of Societe Generale SA fell more than expected.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  